# Orchestrator ‚Äî Update Customer Notes (Stage 3)

**Scope:** When the user runs **Update Customer Notes (UCN)** via **`10-task-router.mdc`**, execute the steps below **in order**. Treat any of these as **the same default pipeline** (including **Phase 0** ‚Äî built-in Challenge Review), normalizing **`[CustomerName]`** like **`docs/project_spec.md` ¬ß2 Rule 4**:

- **`Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`**
- **`UCN for [CustomerName]`** or informal **`UCN`** / **`ucn`** when the customer is already fixed in thread context
- **`Update Customer Notes with Challenge Review first for [CustomerName]`** / **`Lifecycle-first Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`** (aliases; same behavior as default UCN)

**Opt-out (skip Phase 0 ‚Äî legacy single STOP, Block B only):** Only when the user explicitly asks for **`Update Customer Notes (no challenge review) for [CustomerName]`**, **`UCN without challenge review for [CustomerName]`**, or **`Light UCN for [CustomerName]`**.

This is a **product-run playbook** for the **main Agent in this chat**; it does **not** replace **`.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc`** (repo planner, subagent **`/coder` `/tester` `/doc`** gates, or task-file approval).

**`_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E override (test-only):** when the run is **`Run E2E Test Customer`** for customer **`_TEST_CUSTOMER`**, execute this pipeline end-to-end without approval pauses for write tools (including `update_challenge_state`, `write_doc`, `append_ledger_row`, `write_call_record`, `sync_notes`). Keep normal approval behavior for all other customers/runs. See `.cursor/rules/11-e2e-test-customer-trigger.mdc` and `docs/ai/playbooks/e2e-test-customer.md` for the canonical 10-step sequence.

## Built-in Challenge Review ‚Äî Phase 0 (default)

**Plain English:** Saying **UCN** means the agent **reviews every open challenge** against transcripts and the saved lifecycle snapshot, shows **one review table**, and may propose **challenge status updates** to persist **after you approve**. You do **not** need to know file names or JSON; the agent handles persistence via MCP once you pick **Approve all**, **A only**, **B only**, or edits.

**When:** **Before pipeline Step 1**, unless **Scope ‚Äî opt-out** applies.

1. Run challenge governance inline: read **`challenge-lifecycle.json`** via MCP **`read_challenge_lifecycle`**, merge ids + **last_updated** / state against call records, compute stall/drift per **`docs/ai/references/challenge-lifecycle-model.md`** (‚â• 60 days since last transition on an unresolved state is a stall flag), and emit **one** review table with columns **`challenge_id | description | current_state | last_updated | evidence | stall / risk | recommended_action`**. Reuse data already loaded in orchestrator **Steps 2‚Äì3** where it is equivalent. When UCN is the parent run, **do not** use a **second** STOP for this ‚Äî lifecycle write proposals are folded into **Block A** below.
2. Build **Block A ‚Äî Challenge status updates** (implementation: MCP **`update_challenge_state`** rows: `challenge_id`, `new_state`, `evidence` citing **`call_id`** or lifecycle rule). Only **legal single-step** transitions per **`prestonotes_mcp/journey.py`**. Rows may be **zero**.
3. **Do not** call **`update_challenge_state`** until the combined approval step below.

**Steps 1‚Äì7** ‚Äî Same as the default pipeline, with these **additions**:

- Treat **`MyNotes/Customers/[CustomerName]/AI_Insights/challenge-lifecycle.json`** (read via MCP **`read_challenge_lifecycle`**) as **+1** source when compiling **`challenge_tracker`** / exec narrative so **Block B** (mutation JSON) **does not contradict** Block A once both are approved.
- If the user will approve **Block B only**, Phase 0 still ran so the doc plan is **informed** by the review table; **skip executing** Block A in that case.

**STOP ‚Äî combined user review (default UCN)**

Present in **one** message:

1. **Block A** ‚Äî Table of proposed **`update_challenge_state`** rows (or **‚Äúnone proposed‚Äù**).
2. **Block B** ‚Äî Plain-language summary, **mutation JSON** for **`write_doc`**, proposed **ledger** row, **`write_doc` `dry_run=true`** preview when available.
3. Say explicitly: **Approve all (A then B), Block B only, Block A only, or reject / edit.** **No** **`update_challenge_state`**, **`write_doc`**, **`append_ledger`**, **`append_ledger_row`**, **`sync_notes`** for mutation purposes until the user answers.

**STOP ‚Äî legacy (opt-out UCN only)**

After Step 7, if Phase 0 was **skipped**: present **Block B** only (summary, mutation JSON, ledger, dry run) ‚Äî same mutation gate as **`.cursor/rules/core.mdc`**. **No** **`update_challenge_state`** unless the user separately requested lifecycle writes.

**Execute (only after explicit approval)**

1. **If Block A approved (in full or in part):** run **`update_challenge_state`** once per **approved** row **before** any **`write_doc`**. Every call must obey the **Challenge lifecycle write rules** in **`.cursor/rules/21-extractor.mdc`** (TASK-048) ‚Äî notably `transitioned_at` is the cited transcript's call date (not the run date) and `evidence` must be free of harness vocabulary from `FORBIDDEN_EVIDENCE_TERMS` in **`prestonotes_mcp/journey.py`**.
2. **If Block B approved:** run **`write_doc`** with MCP **`customer_name`** set to **`[CustomerName]`** whenever known (enables lifecycle ‚Üî Challenge Tracker parity checks in `update-gdoc-customer-notes.py`), then **`append_ledger_row`** (or **`append_ledger`** for the legacy GDoc ledger-append path). **Challenge Tracker rows** in the mutation plan must obey the **Challenge Tracker row discipline** in **`.cursor/rules/21-extractor.mdc`** (¬ßB.1) ‚Äî call-date `date` column, only transcript-backed evidence dates, no harness vocabulary.
3. Optional **`log_run`**, then **`sync_notes`** (when local mirror / Drive policy expects it), same as the default path.
4. If the user approved **Block B only**, **skip** step **1** entirely ‚Äî still run steps **2**, **3**.

The narrative view of the account (Health line, call spine, milestones, challenge review, stakeholder evolution) now lives in **`Run Account Summary for [CustomerName]`** (**`docs/ai/playbooks/run-account-summary.md`**). UCN writes persisted state ‚Äî **`challenge-lifecycle.json`**, the Google Doc, and the History Ledger ‚Äî and nothing more.

